properties.otherAdvice:
The Everest Carnival - Epsom Day at Royal Randwick Racecourse from 12:25pm.

Traffic may be heavier on roads around the racecourse including Anzac Pde, Doncaster Ave, High St, Alison Rd and Darley Rd.

Special event clearway parking restrictions will be in effect on sections of Ascot St from 8am to 7pm and High St from 3pm to 7pm.

Clearways are strict no-parking zones, and apply even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

webLinks.linkText: Rotary Newcastle to Dungog Charity Bike Ride

properties.headline: Charity Bike Ride - Saturday 26 September - NEWCASTLE TO DUNGOG via Hexham Bridge, Pacific Hwy, Maitland Rd
properties.adviceB: Allow extra travel time; Exercise caution
properties.otherAdvice:
Up to 300 cyclists will participate in the Rotary Charity Newcastle to Dungog bike ride leaving in groups from Queens Wharf, Newcastle at 6.30am to finish at Jubilee Park in Dungog by 1.30pm.

Cyclists will ride 90km from Newcastle to Dungog travelling via Wharf Rd, Workshop Way, Honeysuckle Dr, Hannell St, Industrial Dr, Maitland Rd, Pacific Hwy (Hexham Bridge), The Bucketts Way, Limeburners Creek Rd, Glen Martin Rd, Pine Brush Rd, Alison Rd and Stroud Hill Rd.

Traffic control will be in place northbound on Hexham Bridge, including a left lane closure, between 6am and 10am, as cyclists travel across the bridge. The speed limit will also be reduced from 80km/h to 40km/h.

Motorists should be aware of the groups of cyclists as they share roads throughout the event. Motorists are also reminded when overtaking cyclists to leave a 1.5m distance on roads with speed limits over 60km/h and a 1m distance on roads 60km/h or under.

roads.mainStreet: via Hexham Bridge, Pacific Hwy, Maitland Rd
